Maggard 2-Band Badger Brush Now Available!
Brad on December 28, 2016 in News, Store | No Comments » 

Introducing the first Maggard Badger brush!  With a solid Aluminum handle, and matte gray finish, it’s not only a great performer, but also a beautiful addition to any shaving kit.   Priced at only $24.95, it’s sure to be a hit.





Economy International Shipping starts October 12, 2016
Brad on October 10, 2016 in News, Store | 11 Comments » 

We will be going live with Economy International shipping rates on Tuesday, October 11, and we will begin shipping International Economy on Wednesday, October 12. On top of Edge membership programs being offered to 28 countries ($29.95 – 39.95), all other international orders will be discounted up to 70% off of current rates.
NOTE:  WE HAVE SINCE ENDED FREE INTERNATIONAL SHIPPING ON LARGE ORDER SIZES & INTERNATIONAL EDGE MEMBERSHIPS.  Sorry!  HOWEVER – we’ve further discounted rates by another 20%+!
Existing EDGE Memberships will be honored until their expiration dates.  Thank you for those who participated in this experiment!
We will also be offering free Economy International shipping on the following order sizes, site wide:

$115+ Free Shipping to Canada & Mexico
$150+ Free shipping to 26 Countries (Argentina, Australia, Austria, Belgium, Brazil, Denmark, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hong Kong, Israel, Italy, Japan, Netherlands, New Zealand, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Republic of Ireland, Singapore, South Korea, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, United Kingdom (UK)
$200+ Free Shipping to any other country we ship to not mentioned above

We’re very excited about being able to offer this to our customers across the world. Specifically, a tremendous selection of Artisan soaps will finally have a way to cost effectively get into the hands of a large portion of the world. We think it will not only be great for our business, but will increase the exposure and business of some of the amazing products being produced by our community.




The Maggard Slant Razor is Finally Here!
Brad on September 7, 2016 in News | 3 Comments » 

After 1.5 years of attempts, we finally have a product we feel is worthy of the Maggard name.





